g.text: TX side of PMD will pass the address (or offset) of the packet address to TX RingTX packet data is placed at the following address•addr = (char *)mbuf + sizeof(pktmbuf_t);•addr += XDP_PACKET_HEADROOM;•addr += xdp_umem.head_room; // (normally zero)•Descriptor Address uses the above locationTX Ring returns packet offset address•Need to AND off the lower bits of the address using ~(2048 -1) 0x7ff to get to the mbuf pointer.
Packet data starts at 256 bytes offset from buffer XDP_PACKET_HEADROOM
